      "writtenOn": "2018-06-12T19:11:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In practice they all are currently contiguous. I thought about requiring that and still could. I didn\u0027t see anything that got simplified (other than this debug code) by imposing that requirement, though. There\u0027s a slightly looser possible requirement: making them be sorted by offset and non-overlapping.\n\nAnother option I thought about but didn\u0027t attempt was to make the attributes a linked list and to make the offset implicit. There is a small downside that a GP could only have static constexpr attributes if all its attributes are known at compile time (or I suppose it could have separate static constexpr attribute sets for each runtime possibility).",
